parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine wiring harness can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down, leading to accidents or fires, and may also result in expensive repairs to other vehicle systems.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts down
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle experiences sudden acceleration or loss of power
smoke or fire from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine head gasket failure can cause engine oil to leak into the oil pan, leading to engine failure, stalling, or overheating, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: oil seepage into the oil pan

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent electrical system issues can cause engine stalling, erratic engine behavior, and loss of power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
A defective engine wiring harness can cause engine overheating, blown head gaskets, and electrical system issues, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Incomplete or Missing Rear Wheel Well Panel
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incomplete or missing rear wheel well panel can cause debris to be thrown into the vehicle, potentially damaging the vehicle's interior and exterior components, and creating a hazardous driving environment.
